# Spectral — Deployment

## Environment Variables (complete list)

### Production (Vercel dashboard — never commit to repo)
```
# Supabase
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=          ← server-only, never NEXT_PUBLIC_

# Anthropic
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=                  ← server-only, never NEXT_PUBLIC_

# Mapping
NEXT_PUBLIC_CESIUM_ION_TOKEN=       ← domain-restricted, safe to expose
NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN=           ← domain-restricted, safe to expose

# App
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://spectral.a3dm.com.au
```

### Local (.env.local — gitignored)
Same keys, pointing to local/staging Supabase instance.

## Pre-Deploy Checklist

Run through every time before `git push` to main:

```
□ All env vars present in Vercel dashboard (check Settings → Environment Variables)
□ Supabase migrations applied to production (supabase db push)
□ No SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in client-side code
   grep -r "SERVICE_ROLE\|ANTHROPIC_API" app/
□ Classification banner present and non-removable in layout
□ CesiumJS dynamic imports all have ssr:false
□ No top-level 'cesium' imports (would break SSR)
   grep -r "from 'cesium'" app/ components/
□ Build passes locally: npm run build
□ No TypeScript errors: npm run type-check
□ Lint clean: npm run lint
```

## Migration Process

```bash
# 1. Write migration file
supabase migration new add_scenario_injects_table

# 2. Edit supabase/migrations/[timestamp]_add_scenario_injects_table.sql

# 3. Test locally
supabase db reset   # applies all migrations from scratch

# 4. Apply to production
supabase db push    # apply pending migrations to linked project

# 5. Verify
supabase db diff    # should show no diff after push
```

## Vercel Build Settings

```
Framework Preset: Next.js
Root Directory: ./
Build Command: npm run build
Output Directory: .next
Install Command: npm install
Node.js Version: 20.x
```

## CesiumJS Static Assets (must be in vercel.json)

```json
{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/static/Cesium/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "public, max-age=31536000, immutable" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

The CopyWebpackPlugin in `next.config.ts` handles copying Cesium assets to `public/static/Cesium/` at build time. Do not modify this config.

## Rollback Procedure

### Code rollback (Vercel)
1. Go to Vercel dashboard → Deployments
2. Find last known-good deployment
3. Click ⋯ → Promote to Production
4. Takes effect immediately (no rebuild)

### Database rollback
Supabase does not support automatic migration rollback. Procedure:
1. Write a reverse migration: `supabase migration new rollback_[feature_name]`
2. The reverse migration must be the inverse of the forward migration
3. Apply: `supabase db push`
4. Always write rollback migrations at the same time as forward migrations

## Post-Deploy Smoke Tests

```
□ /login — loads, can authenticate
□ /library — loads platform list (confirms Supabase read working)
□ /spectrum — D3 chart renders (confirms client-side JS bundle working)
□ /arena — CesiumJS globe loads (confirms static asset delivery working)
□ /api/health — returns 200 (basic route handler health)
□ Classification banner visible on all pages
□ No console errors in browser
```

## Monitoring

- Vercel Analytics: enabled for all deployments
- Supabase Dashboard: watch for query errors and RLS violations after deploy
- Browser console: no unhandled errors on core module pages
